    "heroImageUrl": "https://panel.aushenstone.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/guide-for-cleaning-bluestone-pavers.jpg",
    "excerpt": "Ignoring the natural beauty of bluestone is very tough. It is one of the most popular paving products on the earth that makes any open space more stylish and attractive. Whether...",
    "bodyHtml": "<p>Ignoring the natural beauty of bluestone is very tough. It is one of the most popular paving products on the earth that makes any open space more stylish and attractive. Whether you want to design the patio, welcoming pathway, or garden area or beautify the swimming deck area, <a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/bluestone/\"><strong>bluestone pavers</strong></a> can be used for multiple purposes in commercial and residential properties.</p><p>However, like many other porous materials, bluestone pavers can become worn, stained and tired-looking if not cleaned or maintained properly. Experts recommend regular cleaning and sealing of your <strong>bluestone pavers in Melbourne</strong> to make them look their best for years to come.</p><h3 id=\"how-to-clean-your-bluestone-paving\">How To Clean Your Bluestone Paving</h3><p>Cleaning <strong>bluestone pavers</strong> is undoubtedly challenging and daunting, but cleaning them is essential to maintain their natural beauty and durability. Here is an 8-step DIY guide for an effective cleaning process:</p><ol><li>Sweep the pavers thoroughly to remove any loose debris or dirt.</li><li>Prepare a cleaning solution by mixing water and a mild detergent or soap.</li><li>With the help of a soft-bristled brush or a cloth, apply the solution to the pavers and leave it for 15 minutes.</li><li>After 15 minutes, scrub the pavers thoroughly, paying special attention to any stains or marks.</li><li>Rinse the pavers with clean water to remove any soap residue.</li><li>To remove stubborn stains, use a specialized acid-free stone cleaner or a mixture of white vinegar and water.</li><li>Let the pavers air dry completely. If the pavers are still dirty, repeat the above process.</li><li>Consider applying a sealer to protect the pavers and keep them looking their best.</li></ol><p>By following the above steps, you can effectively clean your bluestone pavers and enhance their longevity.</p><p><strong>Tip:</strong> To ensure whether any cleaning solution is suitable for your pavers or not, always test it in an inconspicuous area first.</p><h3 id=\"stay-in-touch-with-aushen-stone-andamp-tile\">Stay in Touch With Aushen Stone &amp; Tile</h3><p>At <strong><a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/\">Aushen Stone &amp; Tile</a></strong>, we pride ourselves on providing expert knowledge and excellent customer service for things related to bluestone paving. So if you are looking for bluestone pavers in Melbourne at an affordable price, look no further than our stunning collection of bluestone pavers.</p><p>For more information on choosing and installing the right pavers for your property, give us a call at <a href=\"tel:+61430799906\"><strong>0430 799 906</strong></a>.</p>",
