    "excerpt": "Nothing beats a stylish in-ground swimming pool for adding value to any outdoor space while also providing relief from the scorching heat of summer. However, constructing an...",
    "bodyHtml": "<p>Nothing beats a stylish in-ground swimming pool for adding value to any outdoor space while also providing relief from the scorching heat of summer. However, constructing an appealing, safe and durable pool can be tricky unless you know how to choose the best pavers and coping. You can find various artificial and natural <a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/\"><strong>pavers in Melbourne</strong></a> to create long-lasting and exceptional pool decks.</p><p>Choosing the right pool pavers is essential for increasing the beauty and functionality of your outdoor space. Remember, the right pool paving will withstand exposure to salt, chlorine and other chemicals and won’t get too hot or be too slippery under wet feet. So let’s dive into some expert tips that you must consider when choosing pool pavers and pool coping for your setting.</p><h3 id=\"1-appearance\">1) Appearance</h3><p>When selecting pool pavers, it is vital to look for the right colour and texture of the paver that compliments your pool and its surrounding features, the character of your home and your taste. Also, consider whether the stone you choose fits the architectural style of your property or not.</p><h3 id=\"2-durability\">2) Durability</h3><p>Swimming pools usually use chlorine, salt and other chemicals in the water to prevent algae and bacterial growth. Due to the constant exposure to such chemicals, you must choose a suitable paving material that can withstand wear and tear from frequent use and furniture.</p><h3 id=\"3-slip-resistance\">3) Slip Resistance</h3><p>In addition to providing an attractive look to your pool, you’ll need to select a paver with an anti-slip surface to avoid accidents and injuries, given the pavers will be wet most of the time. For instance, bluestone in a sawn finish offers a good footing and avoids the perils of slipping as compared to a honed paver.</p><h3 id=\"4-pool-coping\">4) Pool Coping</h3><p>Whether you want to run the paving along the edge of your pool or use a different material for the pool coping, choose a pool paver that not only integrates with the rest of the landscape and appeals aesthetically but performs well. From a modern drop face to a smooth bullnose, a wide range of matching coping is available to suit your needs.</p><h3 id=\"to-conclude\">To Conclude</h3><p>At Aushen Stone &amp; Tile, we have a complete range of pool pavers and pool coping options in Melbourne to suit the precise needs of your property. We are proud to stock the best quality <a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/bluestone/\"><strong>bluestone pavers in Melbourne</strong></a> that are ideal for creating a timeless look and adding a flawless finish to your swimming pool. From <a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/granite/\"><strong>granite pool coping</strong></a> to travertine paving, we can discuss the many options available to help you create a swimming pool that will look amazing for many years.</p><p>For more advice on choosing the right pool pavers and pool coping, call the <a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/\"><strong>Aushen Stone &amp; Tile</strong></a> team at <a href=\"tel:+61430799906\"><strong>0430 799 906</strong></a>.</p>",
