    "excerpt": "Granite is formed from cooled and solidified volcanic magma. Owing to their exemplary hardness, stone fabricators avoided working with them in historic times. But in recent times...",
    "bodyHtml": "<p>Granite is formed from cooled and solidified volcanic magma. Owing to their exemplary hardness, stone fabricators avoided working with them in historic times. But in recent times, granites have gained widespread popularity for their strength, resilience, and variety of shades.</p><p><a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/granite/\"><strong>Granite pool coping tiles</strong></a> are a widely accepted paving solution for the backyard of any swimming pool area. Here’s a list of reasons why pavers in Melbourne use granite pool coping the most.</p><h3 id=\"1-durability\">1) Durability</h3><p>Granite tiles are one of the most durable materials for your pool. They are highly flexible and have scratch-resistant, chip-resistant, and stain-resistant properties. Granite pool coping tiles can withstand all types of extreme Australian weather conditions much better than any other natural stone.</p><h3 id=\"2-water-and-moisture-resistant\">2) Water and Moisture Resistant</h3><p>Due to its impermeable nature, granite has outstanding water-resistant properties, making it virtually impenetrable. Granite pool coping easily resists the splashes of salty and chlorinated pool water.</p><h3 id=\"3-aesthetic-appeal\">3) Aesthetic Appeal</h3><p>Granite offers a rugged, minimalistic look with a wide range of colours and designs that come from the minerals present in it. This gives a great opportunity to select the right material that fits your backyard’s theme and complements the pool deck.</p><h3 id=\"4-affordability\">4) Affordability</h3><p>Due to their abundant availability, granite pavers and tiles offer a glorious charm to your exteriors at affordable prices. Furthermore, due to its durability, impermeability, and damage-resistant properties, you will have negligible maintenance costs in the long run.</p><h3 id=\"5-safety\">5) Safety</h3><p>Even when wet, granite pavements offer a strong grip for your feet, making them the safest option for any swimming pool. Additionally, it holds no moisture or water, so any water falling off the pool can easily be guided to slide off the deck.</p><p>If you want to add <strong>granite coping tiles</strong> to your backyard in Melbourne, rush to your closest <a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/\"><strong>Aushen Stone &amp; Tile</strong></a> outlet. As one of the leading <strong>granite pavers</strong> operating all over Melbourne, we offer an extensive range of designs and materials.</p><p>For more information about us, call us at <a href=\"tel:+61430799906\"><strong>0430 799 906</strong></a> or drop us an email at <a href=\"mailto:info@aushenstone.com.au\"><strong>info@aushenstone.com.au</strong></a> NOW!</p>",
