    "excerpt": "Many people have been using travertine as a building material for centuries because it is durable and beautiful. Travertine is considered the Best Pool Coping in Melbourne with its...",
    "bodyHtml": "<p>Many people have been using travertine as a building material for centuries because it is durable and beautiful. Travertine is considered the Best <a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/application/pool-coping/\"><b>Pool Coping in Melbourne </b></a> with its engraving features and easy installation.</p><p>At <b>Aushen Stone</b>, you can choose from many different shapes, such as rectangular or square pieces of stone, to more creative options like hexagonal slabs that are tough enough in Even heavy snowfall without permanently discolouring your floor!</p><h3 id=\"travertine-a-natural-stone-that-looks-great-with-any-pool\">Travertine - A Natural Stone That Looks Great With Any Pool</h3><ul><li>Travertine is a natural stone that can enhance the look of any swimming pool.</li><li>It is available in a variety of colours, and it can be polished to a high sheen or left with a more rustic appearance.</li><li>Travertine is also very durable, making it an ideal choice for pool areas that are likely to be subjected to heavy use.</li><li>By choosing travertine for your pool area, you will create a beautiful and stylish space that family and friends will enjoy for years to come.</li><li>This natural stone looks unmatched by any other material, and it coordinates well with any pool design.</li><li>In addition to its great looks, travertine is also incredibly durable and long-lasting. If you are thinking about adding some new pavers to your pool area, be sure to consider travertine!</li></ul><h3 id=\"customised-colours-to-match-the-rest-of-your-backyard-landscape\">Customised Colours To Match The Rest Of Your Backyard Landscape</h3><ul><li>Unlike other stones with only a specific colour palette, travertine can be customised to match your design preferences with matching colours or patterns.</li><li>You can always enhance the look of your travertine stone by adding grooves and trenches.</li><li>Travertine is the perfect way to liven up any backyard with a colour palette as customisable and versatile as your imagination.</li><li>You can customise it with matching colours or patterns that fit into other aspects of landscaping you have in this area - from exterior design themes all across town down through specific plant lists for individual styles!</li><li>The palette could also be changed according-to preferences related specifically around garden landscapes else where nearby so as not to make it stand out too much against its surroundings!</li></ul><h3 id=\"durable-and-beautiful-building-material\">Durable And Beautiful Building Material</h3><p><a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/travertine/\">Travertine</a> is a popular choice for pool coping as the stone engraves many different features, such as <a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/application/roofing/\"><b>roofing</b></a> and <a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/application/stone-paving/\"><b>paving</b></a>. However, this beautiful material has always been used in construction.</p><p>It can also provide an excellent finish when applied to surfaces that require polishing or tiled patterns like floors of commercial and residential flooring spaces.</p><h3 id=\"wrap-up\">Wrap-Up</h3><p>People have been using travertine as a building material for centuries. It is durable, beautiful, and can be used in all shapes to suit your needs.</p><p>Are you thinking about which shape would work best for your space?</p><p>We are happy to help you find suitable travertine for your building project. For further assistance, <a href=\"https://aushenstone.com.au/contact-us/\"><b>get in touch</b></a> with our team of experts today at <a href=\"mailto:info@aushenstone.com.au\"><b>info@aushenstone.com.au</b></a></p>",
